    "In contrast, continu- ous optimisation treats the adjacency matrix as a real-valued matrix.",
    "As with non-continuous score-based methods the goal of continuous optimisation is to maximise how well the DAG fits the data, but the requirement for acyclicity is expressed as an equality constraint on real values making the method an equality constrained problem (Vowels et al. 2021).",
    "One of the key advantages of this approach is that it is much closer to approaches used in mainstream machine learning and allows the use of powerful off-the-shelf optimisation approaches.",
